					<head>Perush Mishle</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Gersonides (Leṿi ben Gershom aka Ralbag) on the book of Proverbs, with the punctuated and accentuated biblical text.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="87v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Mishle</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש משלי</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/59118174">Levi ben Gershom        </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/59118174">לוי בן גרשם</persName>
							</author>
							<explicit xml:lang="he">ובכאן נשלם ספר הביאור ת&apos;ל&apos;ח&apos; חזק ונתחזק ביראת חזק ולעד לא נזק אמן.<locus n="85v"/>
							</explicit>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex, Italian (Ashkenazi style) square and semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of c15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">87 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120</height>
										<width>80</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>87 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end; folios 1-2 and 87 are paper).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout ruledLines="37" writtenLines="37" columns="2">
									<p>Punctuated and accentuated biblical text is embedded.</p>
									<p>Hard-point ruling is visible.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian (Ashkenazi style) square and semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 3r to 5v contain three poetical elegies.</p>
							<p>Folio 6v contains a list of accents of the three poetical books.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Yehudah ben Shelomoh Yedidyah</name>, inscribed in the contract of sale to Eliezer ben Eliyahu of Aquila, witnessed by Menaḥem ben Eliyahu of Ascoli and Yeḳutiel ben Mosheh of Sulmona, folio 86v, with a date of 226 (1465). </p>
							<p>A former owner&apos;s seal, folio 3r: Pandulphi de Ricasolio Baronibus Cano. Flor., dated 1654.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. brown tooled leather.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
